task.summary: Default task
Adds flexibility to Request, exposes setters for a few request headers. Adds test for Request.
Url queue switch to ArrayDeque, from LinkedList. Bug fix for UrlQueue.toList(). Added file extensions to blacklist.
Refactored from package-by-layer to something closer to package-by-feature
Adds improvements to crawlable url discovery, adds protocol whitelist,
Fixes for bugs discovered during testing
Fixes for robotsTxt parse bugs, adds some logger output, adds maven config for creating a distributable jar-with-dependencies for testing
Migrates URL filtering logic to URLFilter class
crawler now publish crawl results as JSON to messaging service

Migrates URLfiltering logic out of URLQueue Refactors application to use URI class to represent addresses instead of URL in order to address major headaches with URL class's .equals() running a an unnecessary blocking IP lookup everytime a comparison is made Adds CrawlerSettings class that will load application settings from a config file
Fixes for URLQueue unit test failures introduced during URL to URI refactoring
Removes messaging facade and exposes queues instead, adds Environment class that reads environment settings from file
Adds gzip compression to crawl results, adds unit tests for gzip compression
Bug fixes - Messaging layer now properly declares gzip content encoding header, Domain.toJSON() now maps page path & query to the page source, instead of placing page sources in a List
Resolves a headaches from character encoding issues between different systems by converting to base64 before publishing to messenger, adds compression unit tests
Requests now accommodate a response code of 0, for debugging purposes
Domain crawlers will now actively seek out sitemap from their robots.txt and attempt to crawl sitemap first
crawler thread count now declared at runtime as an argument, bugfix for robots.txt lookup, cleaned up some unused imports
Fixes bug where page parser would miss new line characters
adds small improvement to robots.txt parser
